text: John James Warr (16 July 1927 - 9 May 2016) was an English cricketer. He was a successful county player for Middlesex County Cricket Club. He played two Test matches for England. With his Test bowling average remains the worst of any retired English player. Warr was known for his sense of humour and made many humorous after dinner speeches. He was born in Ealing, Middlesex, England, Warr died on 9 May 2016, aged 88. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:2016 deaths Category:English and Welsh cricketers Category:People from Ealing
title: John Warr
